{"TopicId":201551,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"In today\u0026#039;s \u0026quot;I\u0026#039;ll believe it when I see it\u0026quot; news","CreatedByName":"NFUN","CreatedById":78715,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-08T22:49:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NFUN","CreatedById":78715,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-08T22:49:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/science/energy/a36065327/nuclear-reactor-makes-fusion-viable-by-2030/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWishful thinking? Funding request? Promising advancement? You decide!\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-08T23:15:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think \u002210 years\u0022 might just break off that asymptotic exponential threshold and make it start actually getting closer to fruition.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngrybobH","CreatedById":165814,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T00:29:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe article reads more like an advertisement than anything else. It was light on actual information. I\u0027ll file it under wishful thinking with a touch of looking for investment money so they can figure out what seems to be an extremely long list of technologies they need to make it work before they go broke.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T01:37:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223951312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617928151\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AngrybobH\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, AngrybobH said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe article reads more like an advertisement than anything else. It was light on actual information. I\u0027ll file it under wishful thinking with a touch of looking for investment money so they can figure out what seems to be an extremely long list of technologies they need to make it work before they go broke.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, there\u0027s nothing in this article that says\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ewhat\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0they are doing, only\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E they claim to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T01:56:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat ive learned following polywell and other small scale fusion concepts is how far they are behind tokamaks in their development/testing. they might come out ahead in the long run, when they need to solve the economy problems with gargantuan tokamaks beyond engineering breakeven. but i very much doubt they will be first.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nat worst i think some of them are trolling for patents. they know fusion is coming and if they can patent the one or two little tricks that make it all work, they would be in a good financial situation later on. they are doing real research, so i cant really fault them for wanting a return on investment. if you buy stock in one or more of those companies you could be rich in 30-100 years.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T03:27:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh yes, nuclear fusion as an energy source, \u003Cem\u003Ejust ten years away\u003C/em\u003E. Should be right on time to power my flying car!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T04:51:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHas anybody already patented \u0022concrete support for fusion reactors\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T06:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re making the leap straight to proton-boron fusion, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T13:15:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223951271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617922180\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278715\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NFUN\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, NFUN said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/science/energy/a36065327/nuclear-reactor-makes-fusion-viable-by-2030/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWishful thinking? Funding request? Promising advancement? You decide!\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPopular Mechanics.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027nuff said?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T19:48:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223951505\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617974117\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv c